terms.medium_def:
A man from the tribe of Naphtali living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.24; 
referred to as Jezer (יֵ֫צֶר), or Jezerite (יִצְרִי); 
son of Naphtali; 
a brother of Jahzeel, Guni and Shillem. § the 3rd son of Naphtali and the founder of the family of Jezerites

A man from the tribe of Levi living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.25.3; 
referred to as Zeri (צְרִי), or Izri (יִצְרִי); 
son of Jeduthun; 
a brother of Obed-edom, Mattithiah, Gedaliah, Jeshaiah and Hashabiah. § a leader of one of the Levitical sanctuary choirs

